<task id="dg-configuring-actions-menus-toolbar">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="steven_higgs" timestamp="20150818T111355+0300" comment="The steps are only for configuring actions. There&apos;s nothing about Menus or toolbars. Need to figure a better way to present this whole section."?>Configure
    Actions, Menus, and Toolbars for a Framework<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>You can configure actions, menus, and toolbars that are specific to a <xref
          keyref="glossentry_framework"><term>framework</term></xref> (document type) in the
          <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode to gain a productive editing experience, by using the
          <xref href="../topics/the-document-type-dialog.dita#the-document-type-dialog"
            ><uicontrol>Document Type</uicontrol> configuration dialog box</xref>.</p>
      <p>To add or configure actions, menus, or toolbars follow this procedure:</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="procedure-dg-author-settings">
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to
            <uicontrol>Document Types Association</uicontrol>, and select the <term>framework</term>
          for which you want to create an action.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol> and in the <xref
            href="../topics/the-document-type-dialog.dita#the-document-type-dialog"
              ><uicontrol>Document Type</uicontrol> configuration dialog box</xref> go to the
            <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> tab, then go to <uicontrol>Actions</uicontrol>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Add16.png" id="image_p55_2t4_5r"
            />New</uicontrol> button and use the <xref
            href="../topics/the-action-dialog.dita#the-action-dialog"><uicontrol>Action</uicontrol>
            dialog box</xref> to create an action.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
